<section style="max-width: 65ch;">
  <p class="section-label">— ABOUT</p>

  <div class="glass-surface" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--body); padding: 24px 26px;">

    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.6em;">
      I think best on grey-sky days, the kind that hold their breath until eight, then split open into gold, <em>like the day had been saving something to say</em>. My real thinking happens speeding through mountains in the rain.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.6em;">
      Sometimes on a sixty-degree afternoon — sun threading through leaves, smoke in my lungs, the ground holding my weight — the universe feels like a single continuous thing. <em>Birth and exhale and shadow, all running on the same rule.</em> I try to build software with that feeling somewhere in the room. Tyagaraja's work moves me, so does jamaica pond, beantown.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.6em;">
      I take things apart to understand them - pure distrust (jk), but because <em>every explanation is smaller than the thing it points to</em>. First principles, every time. What rule does this actually obey, and what happens if I sit with it long enough to find out?
    </p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.6em;">
      I'm self-taught by way of reverse engineering — <em>there is a pattern to entropy, everything is a math function in this (damn) universe.</em>.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.6em;">
      Data scientist is the label that fits in the box. In practice I work in whatever the problem needs — all the unglamorous middle of the stack that decides whether something ships or is just a failed business decision. AI is the new steam engine <em>(howdy howdy, more datacenters)</em>. Not efficient 🤑. Definitely not magic 🧛🏻‍♂️. If it costs too much or runs too slow, <em>it isn't done</em>.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.6em;">
      If you're building infrastructure for AI systems that need to work in production, and our values align — <em>talk to me</em>.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.6em;">
      Welcome to the new industrial revolution.
    </p>

